channel.title: 한국어 기초사전 개발 지원(Open API) - 사전 검색
channel.description: 한국어 기초사전 개발 지원(Open API) - 사전 검색 결과

translation.trans_dfn: For something to move from another place to here.

sense.definition: 직업, 학업 등을 위하여 어떤 곳에 소속되다.

translation.trans_dfn: To belong to an organization for employment, study, etc.

sense.definition: 탈것이 기준이 되는 곳을 향하여 운행하다.

translation.trans_dfn: For a means of transportation to run toward a destination.
For a thing or right to be transferred to someone.
For attention, spotlight, etc., to be concentrated to someone.
For news, correspondence, etc., to be heard by someone.

sense.definition: 전기가 통해서 불이 켜지거나 몸에 전하여지다.

translation.trans_word: get to; be available; pass through
translation.trans_dfn: For electricity to be conducted to produce illumination or cause an electric shock.
For luck, reward, or opportuntity to materialize.
For something to be felt or recalled by someone.
To reach a place that one wants to go to.
For a state to occur in someone or something

sense.definition: 어떤 목적이 있는 모임에 참석하기 위해 다른 곳에 있다가 이곳으로 위치를 옮기다.

translation.trans_dfn: To move from another place to here to attend a gathering that has a certain purpose.
For an unhealthy symptom to appear.

sense.definition: 길이나 깊이가 어떤 정도에 이르거나 닿다.

translation.trans_dfn: For the length or depth to reach or get to a certain degree.
To reach a certain time or period.
For something to be slanted toward a side.

sense.definition: 비, 눈 등이 내리거나 추위 등이 닥치다.

translation.trans_dfn: For the rain, snow, etc., to fall, or for a cold spell to arrive.
For an illness, drowsiness, etc., to appear or occur.
For a time, season, etc., to come.
For something to occur due to a certain cause.
For something to be passed from one place to another.
To pass a path to move toward here.

sense.definition: 어떤 목적이나 일을 위하여 다른 곳에서 이곳으로 위치를 옮기다.

translation.trans_dfn: To move from another place to here for a purpose or business.

sense.definition: 앞의 말이 뜻하는 행동이나 상태가 계속 진행됨을 나타내는 말.

translation.trans_dfn: An auxiliary verb used to indicate that the act or state mentioned in the preceding statement is continued.

sense.definition: 어쩌다가 가끔. 또는 지나는 길에 우연히.

translation.trans_word: occasionally; by chance; once in a while
translation.trans_dfn: Sometimes; accidentally on one's way.

sense.definition: 어떤 물건을 한 곳에서 다른 곳으로 옮겨 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To bring an object from one place to another place.
To bring along an object.
To generate a certain condition or a result.

sense.definition: 목적지를 향하여 다리를 움직여서 이동하여 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To take a step forward in the direction of a destination.

sense.definition: 목적지에 이르기 위하여 어떤 길을 지나오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To come down a certain path to get to a destination.
(figurative) To follow a certain path or evolve.
To come out.
To come surging out of something.
To visit a place for a certain purpose.

sense.definition: 책, 신문, 방송 등에 글이나 그림 등이 실리거나 어떤 내용이 나타나다.

translation.trans_dfn: For writings, pictures, stories, etc., to appear in a newspaper, magazine, broadcast, etc.
To advance into a certain field and begin to work.
For a new product to come out on the market.

sense.definition: 소속된 단체나 직장 등에 일하러 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To come to work in a group or company where one belongs.
To make one's appearance in a place.

sense.definition: 액체나 기체 등이 안에서 밖으로 흐르다.

translation.trans_dfn: For liquid, air, etc., to flow out.
For something to be found or turn up.
For a product to be made or for a certain figure to appear.

translation.trans_word: come from; stem from; originate from
translation.trans_dfn: To emerge from a certain source.
To get out of a certain place and leave.

sense.definition: 소속된 단체나 직장 등에서 일을 그만두고 물러나다.

translation.trans_dfn: To stop working for and leave a group or company where one belongs.
To show a certain attitude toward someone.

translation.trans_word: come out; arrive at a conclusion
translation.trans_dfn: For a result to come out after something is finished.

sense.definition: 받을 돈 등이 주어지거나 세금 등이 물려지다.

translation.trans_word: be paid; be imposed; be charged
translation.trans_dfn: For a wage, allowance, etc., to be paid, or for tax, etc., to be imposed.

sense.definition: 어떤 일을 알리거나 요구하는 서류 등이 전해지다.

translation.trans_dfn: For a document of notifying, requesting for something, etc., to be delivered.

sense.definition: 음식 등이 갖추어져 먹을 수 있게 놓이다.

translation.trans_dfn: For food, etc., to be arranged for someone to eat.

translation.trans_word: come into sight; come into view
translation.trans_dfn: For a destination to come into view.

sense.definition: 무엇을 살 수 있을 정도의 돈이 되다.

translation.trans_dfn: For money, etc., to be provided enough to pay for something.

sense.definition: 방송을 듣거나 볼 수 있게 되다.

translation.trans_dfn: To listen to or watch a broadcast.
For a certain part of something to jut out.
For emotions to be expressed or for physiological phenomenon to appear.

sense.definition: 교육 기관의 일정한 교육 과정을 끝내고 졸업하다.

translation.trans_dfn: To finish a certain course at an educational institution and graudate.
To come to a place for a certain purpose.

sense.definition: 어떤 일에 대한 말이나 평가 등이 나타나다.

translation.trans_word: be mentioned; be released; be raised
translation.trans_dfn: For something to be mentioned or for comments, etc., to be made.

sense.definition: 높은 곳에서 낮은 곳으로 또는 위에서 아래로 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To come from a high place to a lower place, or from up to down.
To come to a rural area from a large city such as Seoul.

sense.definition: 높은 지위에 있다가 낮은 지위로 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To be transferred to a lower position from a high position.
To move from the north to the south.

sense.definition: 계획이나 소식, 또는 명령 등이 위에서 아래로 전달되다.

translation.trans_dfn: For a plan, news, order, etc., to be passed along by a superior so that a subordinate is notified of it.
To approach a certain set point.
To be handed down from the past up until now.

sense.definition: 어떤 장소를 높은 곳에서 낮은 곳으로 옮겨 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To walk down from a high place to a lower place.

sense.definition: 어떤 물건을 높은 곳에서 낮은 곳으로 옮겨 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To carry something from a high place to a lower place.
To go to a certain place and then return from it.

sense.definition: 어떤 일을 하기 위해 갔다가 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To go somewhere to do something and come back.

translation.trans_word: bring someone with one; come in company with
translation.trans_dfn: To make someone follow one, and thus come with him/her.

sense.definition: 원래 있던 곳으로 다시 오거나 다시 그 상태가 되다.

translation.trans_dfn: To come again to where one was before or to be in such a state.
To be one's turn to do something.
To receive something as one's own.
To come the long way.
To have lost the original state of something and to achieve it again.

sense.definition: 일정한 간격으로 되풀이되는 때가 다시 오다.

translation.trans_dfn: For the time that is repeated in regular intervals to come back.

sense.definition: 어떤 장소를 중심으로 원을 그리듯이 움직여 오거나 굽은 길을 지나오다.

translation.trans_dfn: To move around a location as if to draw a circle, or to pass by a curved path.
To come back from the opposite direction from which one came.
